37static const int OUTSIDE_EVEN_TOTAL_SUBSET[] = { 1,10,34,70,126 };
38static const int INSIDE_ODD_TOTAL_SUBSET[] = { 4,20,48,81 };
39static const int OUTSIDE_GSUM[] = { 0,161,961,2015,2715 };
40static const int INSIDE_GSUM[] = { 0,336,1036,1516 };
41static const int OUTSIDE_ODD_WIDEST[] = { 8,6,4,3,1 };
42static const int INSIDE_ODD_WIDEST[] = { 2,4,6,8 };

46static const std::array<FinderCounters, 9> FINDER_PATTERNS = {
47 3,8,2,1,
48 3,5,5,1,
49 3,3,7,1,
50 3,1,9,1,
51 2,7,4,1,
52 2,5,6,1,
53 2,3,8,1,
54 1,5,7,1,
55 1,3,9,1,
56};

72static BitArray::Range
73FindFinderPattern(const BitArray& row, bool rightFinderPattern, FinderCounters& counters)
74{
75 if (row.size() < 2 * 18 + 14)
76 return {row.end(), row.end()};
77
78 return RowReader::FindPattern(
79 // Will encounter white first when searching for right finder pattern
80 // The finder pattern is inside the code, i.e. there must be at least 18 pixels on both sides
81 row.getNextSetTo(row.iterAt(18), !rightFinderPattern), row.end(), counters,
82 [&](BitArray::Iterator b, BitArray::Iterator e, const FinderCounters& counters) {
83 // The finder pattern must have more pixels left and right that it is wide.
84 return ReaderHelper::IsFinderPattern(counters) && (b - row.begin()) > (e - b) && (row.end() - e) > (e-b);
85 });
86}
87
88static RSS::FinderPattern
89ParseFoundFinderPattern(const BitArray& row, int rowNumber, bool right, BitArray::Range range, FinderCounters& finderCounters)
90{
91 if (!range || range.begin == row.begin())
92 return {};
93
94 // Actually we found elements 2-5 -> Locate element 1
95 auto i = std::find(BitArray::ReverseIterator(range.begin), row.rend(), *range.begin);
96 int firstCounter = static_cast<int>(range.begin - i.base());
97 range.begin = i.base();
98
99 // Make 'counters' hold 1-4
100 std::copy_backward(finderCounters.begin(), finderCounters.end() - 1, finderCounters.end());
101 finderCounters[0] = firstCounter;
102 int value = RSS::ReaderHelper::ParseFinderValue(finderCounters, FINDER_PATTERNS);
103 if (value < 0)
104 return {};
105
106 int start = static_cast<int>(range.begin - row.begin());
107 int end = static_cast<int>(range.end - row.begin());
108 if (right) {
109 // row is actually reversed
110 start = row.size() - 1 - start;
111 end = row.size() - 1 - end;
112 }
113
114 return {value,
115 static_cast<int>(range.begin - row.begin()),
116 static_cast<int>(range.end - row.begin()),
117 {ResultPoint(start, rowNumber), ResultPoint(end, rowNumber)}};
118}

120static bool
121AdjustOddEvenCounts(bool outsideChar, int numModules, std::array<int, 4>& oddCounts, std::array<int, 4>& evenCounts,
122 const std::array<float, 4>& oddRoundingErrors, const std::array<float, 4>& evenRoundingErrors)
123{
124 int oddSum = std::accumulate(oddCounts.begin(), oddCounts.end(), 0);
125 int evenSum = std::accumulate(evenCounts.begin(), evenCounts.end(), 0);
126 int mismatch = oddSum + evenSum - numModules;
127 bool oddParityBad = (oddSum & 0x01) == (outsideChar ? 1 : 0);
128 bool evenParityBad = (evenSum & 0x01) == 1;
129
130 bool incrementOdd = false;
131 bool decrementOdd = false;
132 bool incrementEven = false;
133 bool decrementEven = false;
134
135 if (outsideChar) {
136 if (oddSum > 12) {
137 decrementOdd = true;
138 }
139 else if (oddSum < 4) {
140 incrementOdd = true;
141 }
142 if (evenSum > 12) {
143 decrementEven = true;
144 }
145 else if (evenSum < 4) {
146 incrementEven = true;
147 }
148 }
149 else {
150 if (oddSum > 11) {
151 decrementOdd = true;
152 }
153 else if (oddSum < 5) {
154 incrementOdd = true;
155 }
156 if (evenSum > 10) {
157 decrementEven = true;
158 }
159 else if (evenSum < 4) {
160 incrementEven = true;
161 }
162 }
163
164 /*if (mismatch == 2) {
165 if (!(oddParityBad && evenParityBad)) {
166 throw ReaderException.getInstance();
167 }
168 decrementOdd = true;
169 decrementEven = true;
170 } else if (mismatch == -2) {
171 if (!(oddParityBad && evenParityBad)) {
172 throw ReaderException.getInstance();
173 }
174 incrementOdd = true;
175 incrementEven = true;
176 } else */
177 if (mismatch == 1) {
178 if (oddParityBad) {
179 if (evenParityBad) {
180 return false;
181 }
182 decrementOdd = true;
183 }
184 else {
185 if (!evenParityBad) {
186 return false;
187 }
188 decrementEven = true;
189 }
190 }
191 else if (mismatch == -1) {
192 if (oddParityBad) {
193 if (evenParityBad) {
194 return false;
195 }
196 incrementOdd = true;
197 }
198 else {
199 if (!evenParityBad) {
200 return false;
201 }
202 incrementEven = true;
203 }
204 }
205 else if (mismatch == 0) {
206 if (oddParityBad) {
207 if (!evenParityBad) {
208 return false;
209 }
210 // Both bad
211 if (oddSum < evenSum) {
212 incrementOdd = true;
213 decrementEven = true;
214 }
215 else {
216 decrementOdd = true;
217 incrementEven = true;
218 }
219 }
220 else {
221 if (evenParityBad) {
222 return false;
223 }
224 // Nothing to do!
225 }
226 }
227 else {
228 return false;
229 }
230
231 if (incrementOdd) {
232 if (decrementOdd) {
233 return false;
234 }
235 oddCounts[std::max_element(oddRoundingErrors.begin(), oddRoundingErrors.end()) - oddRoundingErrors.begin()] += 1;
236 }
237 if (decrementOdd) {
238 oddCounts[std::min_element(oddRoundingErrors.begin(), oddRoundingErrors.end()) - oddRoundingErrors.begin()] -= 1;
239 }
240 if (incrementEven) {
241 if (decrementEven) {
242 return false;
243 }
244 evenCounts[std::max_element(evenRoundingErrors.begin(), evenRoundingErrors.end()) - evenRoundingErrors.begin()] += 1;
245 }
246 if (decrementEven) {
247 evenCounts[std::min_element(evenRoundingErrors.begin(), evenRoundingErrors.end()) - evenRoundingErrors.begin()] -= 1;
248 }
249 return true;
250}

252static RSS::DataCharacter
253DecodeDataCharacter(const BitArray& row, const RSS::FinderPattern& pattern, bool outsideChar)
254{
255 std::array<int, 8> counters = {};
256
257 if (outsideChar) {
258 if (!RowReader::RecordPatternInReverse(row.begin(), row.iterAt(pattern.startPos()), counters))
259 return {};
260 }
261 else {
262 if (!RowReader::RecordPattern(row.iterAt(pattern.endPos()), row.end(), counters))
263 return {};
264 std::reverse(counters.begin(), counters.end());
265 }
266
267 int numModules = outsideChar ? 16 : 15;
268 float elementWidth = static_cast<float>(std::accumulate(counters.begin(), counters.end(), 0)) / static_cast<float>(numModules);
269
270 std::array<int, 4> oddCounts;
271 std::array<int, 4> evenCounts;
272 std::array<float, 4> oddRoundingErrors;
273 std::array<float, 4> evenRoundingErrors;
274
275 for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
276 float value = (float)counters[i] / elementWidth;
277 int count = (int)(value + 0.5f); // Round
278 //TODO: C++17: count = std::clamp((int)(value + 0.5f), 1, 8);
279 if (count < 1) {
280 count = 1;
281 }
282 else if (count > 8) {
283 count = 8;
284 }
285 int offset = i / 2;
286 if ((i & 0x01) == 0) {
287 oddCounts[offset] = count;
288 oddRoundingErrors[offset] = value - count;
289 }
290 else {
291 evenCounts[offset] = count;
292 evenRoundingErrors[offset] = value - count;
293 }
294 }
295
296 if (!AdjustOddEvenCounts(outsideChar, numModules, oddCounts, evenCounts, oddRoundingErrors, evenRoundingErrors)) {
297 return {};
298 }
299
300 auto calcChecksumPortion = [](const std::array<int, 4>& counts) {
301 int res = 0;
302 for (auto it = counts.rbegin(); it != counts.rend(); ++it) {
303 res = 9 * res + *it;
304 }
305 return res;
306 };
307
308 int checksumPortion = calcChecksumPortion(oddCounts) + 3 * calcChecksumPortion(evenCounts);
309 int oddSum = Reduce(oddCounts);
310 int evenSum = Reduce(evenCounts);
311
312 if (outsideChar) {
313 if ((oddSum & 0x01) != 0 || oddSum > 12 || oddSum < 4) {
314 return {};
315 }
316 int group = (12 - oddSum) / 2;
317 int oddWidest = OUTSIDE_ODD_WIDEST[group];
318 int evenWidest = 9 - oddWidest;
319 int vOdd = RSS::ReaderHelper::GetRSSvalue(oddCounts, oddWidest, false);
320 int vEven = RSS::ReaderHelper::GetRSSvalue(evenCounts, evenWidest, true);
321 int tEven = OUTSIDE_EVEN_TOTAL_SUBSET[group];
322 int gSum = OUTSIDE_GSUM[group];
323 return {vOdd * tEven + vEven + gSum, checksumPortion};
324 }
325 else {
326 if ((evenSum & 0x01) != 0 || evenSum > 10 || evenSum < 4) {
327 return {};
328 }
329 int group = (10 - evenSum) / 2;
330 int oddWidest = INSIDE_ODD_WIDEST[group];
331 int evenWidest = 9 - oddWidest;
332 int vOdd = RSS::ReaderHelper::GetRSSvalue(oddCounts, oddWidest, true);
333 int vEven = RSS::ReaderHelper::GetRSSvalue(evenCounts, evenWidest, false);
334 int tOdd = INSIDE_ODD_TOTAL_SUBSET[group];
335 int gSum = INSIDE_GSUM[group];
336 return {vEven * tOdd + vOdd + gSum, checksumPortion};
337 }
338
339}
340
341static RSS::Pair
342DecodePair(const BitArray& row, bool right, int rowNumber)
343{
344 FinderCounters finderCounters = {};
345
346 auto range = FindFinderPattern(row, right, finderCounters);
347 auto pattern = ParseFoundFinderPattern(row, rowNumber, right, range, finderCounters);
348 if (pattern.isValid()) {
349 auto outside = DecodeDataCharacter(row, pattern, true);
350 if (outside.isValid()) {
351 auto inside = DecodeDataCharacter(row, pattern, false);
352 if (inside.isValid()) {
353 return {1597 * outside.value() + inside.value(), outside.checksumPortion() + 4 * inside.checksumPortion(), pattern};
354 }
355 }
356 }
357 return {};
358}
359
360static void
361AddOrTally(std::list<RSS::Pair>& possiblePairs, const RSS::Pair& pair)
362{
363 if (!pair.isValid()) {
364 return;
365 }
366 for (RSS::Pair& other : possiblePairs) {
367 if (other == pair) {
368 other.incrementCount();
369 return;
370 }
371 }
372// printf("found new pair\n"); fflush(stdout);
373 possiblePairs.push_back(pair);
374}

376static bool
377CheckChecksum(const RSS::Pair& leftPair, const RSS::Pair& rightPair)
378{
379 //int leftFPValue = leftPair.getFinderPattern().getValue();
380 //int rightFPValue = rightPair.getFinderPattern().getValue();
381 //if ((leftFPValue == 0 && rightFPValue == 8) ||
382 // (leftFPValue == 8 && rightFPValue == 0)) {
383 //}
384 int checkValue = (leftPair.checksumPortion() + 16 * rightPair.checksumPortion()) % 79;
385 int targetCheckValue =
386 9 * leftPair.finderPattern().value() + rightPair.finderPattern().value();
387 if (targetCheckValue > 72) {
388 targetCheckValue--;
389 }
390 if (targetCheckValue > 8) {
391 targetCheckValue--;
392 }
393 return checkValue == targetCheckValue;
394}

396static Result
397ConstructResult(const RSS::Pair& leftPair, const RSS::Pair& rightPair)
398{
399 int64_t symbolValue = 4537077 * static_cast<int64_t>(leftPair.value()) + rightPair.value();
400 std::wstringstream buffer;
401 buffer << std::setw(13) << std::setfill(L'0') << symbolValue;
402
403 int checkDigit = 0;
404 for (int i = 0; i < 13; i++) {
405 int digit = buffer.get() - '0';
406 checkDigit += (i & 0x01) == 0 ? 3 * digit : digit;
407 }
408 checkDigit = 10 - (checkDigit % 10);
409 if (checkDigit == 10) {
410 checkDigit = 0;
411 }
412 buffer.put((wchar_t)(checkDigit + '0'));
413
414 auto& leftPoints = leftPair.finderPattern().points();
415 auto& rightPoints = rightPair.finderPattern().points();
416 return Result(buffer.str(), { leftPoints[0], leftPoints[1], rightPoints[0], rightPoints[1] }, BarcodeFormat::RSS_14);
417}
418
419Result
420RSS14Reader::decodeRow(int rowNumber, const BitArray& row_, std::unique_ptr<DecodingState>& state) const
421{
422 if (!state) {
423 state.reset(new RSS14DecodingState);
424 }
425 auto* prevState = static_cast<RSS14DecodingState*>(state.get());
426
427 BitArray row = row_.copy();
428 AddOrTally(prevState->possibleLeftPairs, DecodePair(row, false, rowNumber));
429 row.reverse();
430 AddOrTally(prevState->possibleRightPairs, DecodePair(row, true, rowNumber));
431// row.reverse();
432
433 // To be able to detect "stacked" RSS codes (split over multiple lines)
434 // we need to store the parts we found and try all possible left/right
435 // combinations. To prevent lots of false positives, we require each
436 // pair to have been seen in at least two lines.
437 for (const auto& left : prevState->possibleLeftPairs) {
438 if (left.count() > 1) {
439 for (const auto& right : prevState->possibleRightPairs) {
440 if (right.count() > 1) {
441 if (CheckChecksum(left, right)) {
442 return ConstructResult(left, right);
443 }
444 }
445 }
446 }
447 }
448 return Result(DecodeStatus::NotFound);
449}
